genresAdvancedInfo.name: japanese boom bap
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Japanese boom bap is a style of hip hop music that originated in Japan in the 1990s. It is characterized by its heavy use of samples, particularly from jazz and funk records, and its emphasis on boom bap drum patterns. The music often features socially conscious lyrics and a laid-back, jazzy vibe.
